#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "thag10.3:4.1"
msgid "10.3. Mahākappinattheragāthā"
msgstr ""

#. </h1></div><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a
#. class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc547"></a><a class="verse-num-pts"
#. id="verse-num-pts547"></a>
msgctxt "thag10.3:5.1"
msgid "“Anāgataṃ yo <span class=\"var\" title=\"paṭigacca (bj, pts1)\" id=\"note268\">paṭikacca</span> passati,"
msgstr "If you’re prepared for the future,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:5.2"
msgid "Hitañca atthaṃ ahitañca taṃ dvayaṃ;"
msgstr "Both the good and the bad,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:5.3"
msgid "Viddesino tassa hitesino vā,"
msgstr "Then those who look for your weakness,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:5.4"
msgid "Randhaṃ na passanti samekkhamānā."
msgstr "Whether enemies or well-wishers, will find none."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc548"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts548"></a>
msgctxt "thag10.3:6.1"
msgid "<span class=\"var\" title=\"ānāpānassati (^ps1.3#52 [Ānāpānassatikathā/ Vodānañāṇaniddesa])\" id=\"note269\">Ānāpānasatī</span> yassa,"
msgstr "One who has fulfilled, developed,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:6.2"
msgid "paripuṇṇā subhāvitā;"
msgstr "And gradually consolidated"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:6.3"
msgid "Anupubbaṃ paricitā,"
msgstr "Mindfulness of breathing"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:6.4"
msgid "yathā buddhena desitā;"
msgstr "As taught by the Buddha:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:6.5"
msgid "Somaṃ lokaṃ pabhāseti,"
msgstr "They light up the world,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:6.6"
msgid "abbhā muttova candimā."
msgstr "Like the moon freed from a cloud."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc549"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts549"></a>
msgctxt "thag10.3:7.1"
msgid "Odātaṃ vata me cittaṃ,"
msgstr "Yes, my mind is clean,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:7.2"
msgid "appamāṇaṃ subhāvitaṃ;"
msgstr "Measureless, and well-developed;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:7.3"
msgid "Nibbiddhaṃ paggahītañca,"
msgstr "It is broken through and uplifted—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:7.4"
msgid "sabbā obhāsate disā."
msgstr "It radiates in every direction."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc550"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts550"></a>
msgctxt "thag10.3:8.1"
msgid "Jīvate vāpi sappañño,"
msgstr "The wise person lives on"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:8.2"
msgid "api vittaparikkhayo;"
msgstr "Even after loss of wealth;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:8.3"
msgid "Paññāya ca alābhena,"
msgstr "But without gaining wisdom"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:8.4"
msgid "vittavāpi na jīvati."
msgstr "Even a rich person doesn’t really live."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc551"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts551"></a>
msgctxt "thag10.3:9.1"
msgid "Paññā sutavinicchinī,"
msgstr "Understanding questions what is learned;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:9.2"
msgid "Paññā kittisilokavaddhanī;"
msgstr "Understanding grows fame and reputation;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:9.3"
msgid "Paññāsahito naro idha,"
msgstr "A person who has understanding"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:9.4"
msgid "Api dukkhesu sukhāni vindati."
msgstr "Finds happiness even among sufferings."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc552"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts552"></a>
msgctxt "thag10.3:10.1"
msgid "Nāyaṃ ajjatano dhammo,"
msgstr "It’s not something just for today;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:10.2"
msgid "nacchero napi abbhuto;"
msgstr "It isn’t incredible or astonishing."

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:10.3"
msgid "Yattha jāyetha mīyetha,"
msgstr "When you’re born, you die—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:10.4"
msgid "tattha kiṃ viya abbhutaṃ."
msgstr "What’s astonishing about that?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc553"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts553"></a>
msgctxt "thag10.3:11.1"
msgid "Anantaraṃ hi jātassa,"
msgstr "For anyone who is born,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:11.2"
msgid "jīvitā maraṇaṃ dhuvaṃ;"
msgstr "Death always follows after living."

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:11.3"
msgid "Jātā jātā marantīdha,"
msgstr "Everyone who is born here dies here;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:11.4"
msgid "evaṃdhammā hi pāṇino."
msgstr "Such is the nature of living creatures."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc554"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts554"></a>
msgctxt "thag10.3:12.1"
msgid "Na hetadatthāya matassa hoti,"
msgstr "The things that are useful for the living"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:12.2"
msgid "Yaṃ jīvitatthaṃ paraporisānaṃ;"
msgstr "Are of no use for the dead—not fame, not celebrity,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:12.3"
msgid "Matamhi ruṇṇaṃ na yaso na lokyaṃ,"
msgstr "Not praise by ascetics and brahmins;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:12.4"
msgid "Na vaṇṇitaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇehi."
msgstr "For the dead, there is only weeping."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc555"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts555"></a>
msgctxt "thag10.3:13.1"
msgid "Cakkhuṃ sarīraṃ <span class=\"var\" title=\"upahanti ruṇṇaṃ (bj) | upahanti roṇṇaṃ (s2, s3, pts1-2)\" id=\"note270\">upahanti tena</span>,"
msgstr "And weeping impairs the eye and the body;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:13.2"
msgid "Nihīyati vaṇṇabalaṃ matī ca;"
msgstr "Complexion, health, and intelligence decline."

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:13.3"
msgid "Ānandino tassa disā bhavanti,"
msgstr "Your enemies rejoice;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:13.4"
msgid "Hitesino nāssa sukhī bhavanti."
msgstr "But your well-wishers are not happy."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc556"></a><a class="verse-num-pts"
#. id="verse-num-pts556"></a><a class="pts" id="pts59"></a>
msgctxt "thag10.3:14.1"
msgid "Tasmā hi iccheyya kule vasante,"
msgstr "So you should wish that those who stay in your family"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:14.2"
msgid "Medhāvino ceva bahussute ca;"
msgstr "Have understanding and learning,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:14.3"
msgid "Yesaṃ hi paññāvibhavena kiccaṃ,"
msgstr "And do their duty through the power of understanding,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag10.3:14.4"
msgid "Taranti nāvāya nadiṃva puṇṇan”ti."
msgstr "Just as you’d cross a full river by boat."

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "thag10.3:15.1"
msgid "…"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "thag10.3:15.2"
msgid "Mahākappino thero …."
msgstr ""
